DENGUE/DHF UPDATE 2008 (34): PERU, BRAZIL
*****************************************
A ProMED-mail post
<http://www.promedmail.org>
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
<http://www.isid.org>

In this update:
[1] Peru
[2] Brazil (Ceara)

******
[1] Peru
Date: Sat 2 Aug 2008
Source: Epidemiological Bulletin (Lima) 2008; 17(31), 2008 [in
Spanish, trans. & summ. Mod.TY, edited]
<http://www.oge.sld.pe/boletines/2008/31.pdf>


In EW [epidemiological week] 31 (27 Jul-2 Aug 2008), 20 cases of
classical dengue have been reported by the Directorate General of
Epidemiology from the following Regional Health Units (DIRESAs):
Huanuco 8 cases (40 percent), Jaen 6 cases (30 percent), Luciano
Castillo 3 cases (15 percent) and one case each Pasco, Amazonas, and
Lambayeque.

Loreto and Piura regions are experiencing [a health workers] strike
and they have not reported cases this week.

The accumulated recorded [dengue] cases at the national level are
9529 cases of classic dengue through EW 31 (2008), of which 2268
cases were laboratory confirmed, 5091 are classified as probable
cases, and 2170 have been discarded.

Cases of DHF [dengue hemorrhagic fever] through EW 31 include reports
of 27 cases with 16 being reported as confirmed (5 in Ucayali, 5 in
Piura I, 4 in Loreto, and 2 in Amazonas. There are still 6 classified
as probable cases (2 in Yurimaguas and 1 case each in Iquitos, Rioja,
Sullana, and Jaen) and 5 have been discarded. The DIRESA Piura
reported one death from DHF from Chulucanas, which occurred in EW 23
[1-7 Jun 2008].

The cumulative incidence [of dengue] in the country for the EW 31 is
26.4 per 100 000 inhabitants. The district health areas with highest
incidence and consequently increased risk of transmission are: Loreto
(294.1), Jaen (115.3), Piura II (103.13), Amazonas (101.9), Ucayali
(82.8), Piura I (81.6), San Martin (72.3), Lambayeque (61.6), Madre
de Dios (45.2), Tumbes (35.6), Pasco (21.1), and La Libertad (16.8).

The DIRESAs that are experiencing [dengue] outbreaks are Huanuco and
Piura I. Jaen, with 6 cases notified this week, is once more under alert.

In Lima, 184 dengue [cases] were reported during EW 31. Of the total
cases reported, 142 were discarded; 14 are under review, and 28 have
been confirmed. All confirmed cases are imported [from other regions
of Peru] and come from Iquitos (7 [cases]), Lima (7), Ucayali (4),
Olmos (3), Junin (Chanchamayo) 2, Motupe (1), Guadalupe (La Libertad)
1, La Peca (Amazonas) 1, Patapo (Lambayeque) 1, and Jaen 1 case. No
confirmed locally acquired cases have been reported in Lima.

--
