******
[2] Brazil (Ceara)
Date: Fri 15 Aug 2008
Source: Diario do Nordeste [in Portuguese, trans. & summ. Mod.TY, edited]
<http://diariodonordeste.globo.com:80/noticia.asp?codigo=230330&modulo=966>


Ceara is recording the 2nd largest epidemic of dengue since 1986. The
1st occurred in 1994, with 47 789 recorded [cases] of the disease. In
2008, more than 90 percent of the suspected dengue cases in the 184
municipalities in Ceara have been laboratory confirmed for a total of
37 549 cases. In one week, 414 new cases were recorded. The data is
provided by the weekly bulletin of the Secretariat of Health of the state.

This week, there were no new reports of DHF or dengue with
complications. The number of DHF cases remains the same at 431 and
501 cases of dengue with complications. Another 36 cases are under
investigation. The more severe types of the disease have occurred in
43 cities. Fatal DHF cases were reported from 6 localities.

Forteleza continues to have the greatest number of recorded cases of
DHF, totaling 250, with 8 confirmed deaths and 12 under
investigation. More than 98 percent of the neighborhoods have
confirmed [cases of] classical [dengue] disease.

The state of Ceara has had cases of dengue since 1986, with the
largest epidemics occurring in 1994, 2001, and 2008.

--
Communicated by:
ProMED-PORT
